OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1779987954
OL,3,CPostnatal failings blamed for rising
OL,4,Crates of type 2 diabetes in younger
OL,5,Cwomen
OL,7,FIt usually disappears after birth, but
OL,8,Fpatients face a higher risk of
OL,9,Fdeveloping type 2 diabetes.
OL,11,FAnalysis by Diabetes UK shows that
OL,12,Fdiagnoses of type 2 diabetes in women
OL,13,Funder 40 rose by 47% from 2017/18 to
OL,14,F2023/24, compared to 22% in women aged
OL,15,Fbetween 40 and 79.
OL,17,FThe charity has raised concerns that
OL,18,Fpoor follow-up care for GD, which
OL,19,Faffects between 10% and 20% of
OL,20,Fpregnant women, is contributing to
OL,21,Frising rates.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
